H0.text: What was the first spacecraft to orbit the Earth. Vanguard 1

H1.text: What was the first spacecraft to orbit the Earth. Explorer 1

H2.text: What was the first spacecraft to orbit the Earth. Luna 1

H3.text: What was the first spacecraft to orbit the Earth. Sputnik

A4.text: Sputnik 1 was the first artificial Earth satellite. It was launched into an elliptical low Earth orbit by the Soviet Union on 4 October 1957 as part of the Soviet space program.

A7.text: Vanguard 1 was the fourth artificial Earth-orbiting satellite launched, following Sputnik 1, Sputnik 2, and Explorer 1.

A8.text: The U.S. Navy attempted to put the first U.S. satellite into orbit but failed with the launch of the Vanguard TV-3 on 6 December 1957.

A9.text: Luna 1 became the first human-made object to reach heliocentric orbit and was dubbed 'Artificial Planet 1' and renamed Mechta (Dream).

A10.text: Luna 1 was intended as a Moon impactor, but a malfunction caused it to miss the Moon by 5,900 km and instead enter heliocentric orbit.
